# Testing

Test-first for domain logic. Prefer meaningful tests over coverage padding.

## Structure

Mirror `lib/` under `test/`:

```text
test/
└── features/
    ├── home/
    │   ├── domain/
    │   │   └── usecases/
    │   │       └── has_saved_game_use_case_test.dart
    │   └── presentation/
    │       └── notifiers/
    │           └── home_notifier_test.dart
    ├── game/
    │   ├── domain/
    │   │   └── usecases/
    │   │       └── play_move_use_case_test.dart
    │   ├── fakes/
    │   │   └── fake_game_repository.dart
    │   └── presentation/
    │       ├── notifiers/
    │       │   └── game_notifier_test.dart
    │       └── game_view_test.dart
    └── settings/
        └── domain/
            └── usecases/
                └── set_difficulty_use_case_test.dart

```

Domain tests import Use Cases directly — no `di/` providers needed. Notifier tests override providers from `di/`.

File suffix: `*_test.dart`. One test file per class under test.

## What to test where

| Layer | Type | Depends on | Priority |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Use Cases | Unit | mocks of domain abstractions only | **High** — win/draw, invalid moves, AI |
| Notifier | Unit | `ProviderContainer.test()` + mocked use cases / navigation | Medium |
| View | Widget | `ProviderScope(overrides: [...])` + `pumpWidget` | Low — smoke + key interactions |
| Repository | Unit | fake datasource or in-memory impl | Medium — save/resume (TIC-7) |

Domain unit tests must not import Flutter, Riverpod, GoRouter or platform SDKs.

## Mocks and fakes

Mock only **domain abstractions** (`GameRepository`, `GameNavigation`, etc.).

### Mockito — interactions to verify

Use `mockito` (dev) for dependencies where you need `when` / `verify` (navigation, use cases in Notifier tests).

Manual mocks, no codegen required for this project:

```dart
import 'package:mockito/mockito.dart';

class MockGameNavigation extends Mock implements GameNavigation {}

// when(mockNavigation.openSettings()).thenAnswer((_) async => null);
// verify(mockNavigation.goHome()).called(1);
```

Add `@GenerateMocks([GameRepository])` + codegen only if an interface grows large.

### Manual fakes — stateful behaviour

Prefer a hand-written fake when behaviour is simple and explicit (persistence, in-memory storage):

```dart
final class FakeGameRepository implements GameRepository {
  Game? _saved;

  @override
  Future<Result<Game>> load() async {
    final saved = _saved;
    if (saved == null) {
      return const Result.failure(GameNotFoundError());
    }
    return Result.success(saved);
  }

  @override
  Future<Result<void>> save(Game game) async {
    _saved = game;
    return const Result.success(null);
  }
}

```

Place fakes in `test/features/<feature>/fakes/` or next to the test file.

| Need | Tool |
| --- | --- |
| Verify a method was called (`verify`) | Mockito |
| Simulate save/load with real state | Manual fake |
| Win detection / board logic | Plain domain objects in Arrange — no mock needed |

## Unit test pattern

Arrange / Act / Assert. One behavior per test. Name tests after the scenario:

```dart
test('returns failure when cell is already occupied', () { ... });
test('detects horizontal win on top row', () { ... });
```

## Notifier tests

```dart
final container = ProviderContainer.test(
  overrides: [
    playMoveUseCaseProvider.overrideWithValue(mockUseCase),
  ],
);
addTearDown(container.dispose);

final notifier = container.read(gameNotifierProvider.notifier);

```

Verify state transitions and navigation calls with Mockito `verify` — never depend on GoRouter.

## Widget tests

Wrap with `ProviderScope(overrides: [...])`. Override the Notifier provider or its dependencies.

Test user-visible outcomes (text, enabled/disabled cells), not implementation details.

## Forbidden

- Testing business rules only through widget tests when a Use Case unit test suffices.
- `late` in tests is allowed; `!` remains forbidden.
- Skipping assertions or empty `catch` blocks in test helpers.
